(Data at rest faces threats:) show newline
() show newline
(  * Physical theft) show newline
(  * Disks, servers, backups stolen) show newline
(  * Insider access) show newline
(  * Unauthorized admin access) show newline
(  * Legal compulsion) show newline
(  * Forced disclosure orders) show newline
(  * Decommissioning) show newline
(  * Data remnants on old hardware) show newline
() show newline
(These threats exist regardless of how careful the operators are;) show newline
(encryption transforms security from an operational problem to a) show newline
(cryptographic one.) show newline
() show newline
(Encryption must be:) show newline
() show newline
(  * Transparent) show newline
(  * Applications unaware of encryption) show newline
(  * Performant) show newline
(  * Minimal overhead) show newline
(  * Recoverable) show newline
(  * Key loss doesn't mean data loss) show newline
(  * Auditable) show newline
(  * All key operations logged) show newline
() show newline
(Encryption that applications must think about gets implemented) show newline
(inconsistently; encryption that loses data on key loss is a liability.) show newline
